# Environment Variable Access

- Do not use `process.env` directly in app code.
- Import environment values from `app-config.ts` (preferred) or `lib/env.ts` (backward compat).
- Keep env validation centralized and typed.
- `proxy.ts` (Edge Middleware) is the only exception — it reads `process.env` directly.

## Example

```typescript
// BEST — domain-specific configs
import { plaid, dwolla } from "@/app-config";
const clientId = plaid.PLAID_CLIENT_ID;

// GOOD — backward compat
import { env } from "@/lib/env";
const databaseUrl: string = env.DATABASE_URL;

// BAD — never use process.env directly
const databaseUrl = process.env.DATABASE_URL;
```
